{"word":"ἀτέμβω","slug":"ἀτέμβω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀτέμβω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>Deriv.</a> unknown.\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a>\n<p/><i>to maltreat, to afflict, perplex</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>: <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <i>to be bereft</i> or <i>cheated of</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/>"}]}